Wisconsin, a crucial toss-up state, forced voters to wait in five-hour lines during a shelter-in-place order for its election on April 7.
A lot of progress has been made, Daley argues, but much of it could be reversed by the coronavirus.
We [also] need to be passing laws in states that allow election officials to begin opening and counting and preparing ballots ahead of Election Day.
In Pennsylvania and Michigan, for example, election officials are barred from beginning to open and count the ballots prior to Election Day.